{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Launch a public inquiry into the failures of HS2",
        "additional_details": "We believe politicians and officials responsible must be held accountable for failures relating to HS2. The original cost was around \u00a330 billion; HS2 is now expected to cost over \u00a3100 billion with possible delays and worse service. \r\n \r\nWe believe UK citizens have the right to demand that those responsible for these failures are held accountable. The inquiry should look into putting a provision in place so that decision-making mechanisms in future projects ensure accountability from the outset.",
        "background": "Launch a public inquiry with statutory responsibility to hold to account anyone responsible for the costs on UK taxpayers due to HS2. The inquiry should look at ways to hold accountable those responsible for what we believe has been one of the greatest failures in public spending.",
